        "action": "Improve screening and support for coeliac",
        "additional_details": "This could Improve quality of life; identify health conditions earlier; make people aware; make shopping easier; improve educational attainment and life chances. Some people have silent symptoms of coeliac that mirror other medical conditions.\r\n\r\nIt is estimated 1:100 people have coeliac in the UK \u2013 a gluten sensitivity. If left undiagnosed, it can lead to serious health complications/life limiting conditions. ",
        "background": "The Government should\r\n-Review NICE guidelines on screening and treatment\r\n-Include screening for people with pre-existing conditions (under the NICE guidelines)\r\n-Undertake a national nutritional survey for coeliacs\r\n-Require clearer labelling in colour on front of food packaging for all allergens.",
